    A Record represents all transactions in a time frame. There are yearly, monthly, daily and hourly records. A record is further divided into as many categories, sub categories and sub sub categories as there are defined. The data inside a record should not be modified through a Record, instead use the StatisticsDAO provided by the CoreDAO. It's important to note that child records are not transient, while the parent record is, if there is one.
